[Crim. No. 329. Third Appellate District. October 20, 1915.] In the Matter of the Application of JAMES THOMPSON, on Habeas Corpus. Criminal Law — Commitment — Want oe Probable Cause — Habeas Corpus.—Prisoner discharged on habeas corpus on the authority oí Ess parte Eartwell, ante, p. 627. APPLICATION for a Writ of Habeas Corpus. The facts are similar to those stated in the opinion in Ex parte Hartwell, ante, p. 627, [153 Pac. 730].

Hennessy & Peterson, and James Snell, for Petitioner.

U. S. Webb, Attorney-General, and J. Charles Jones, Deputy Attorney-General, for Respondent.

THE COURT.

This petition is based upon the proceedings in Ex parte Hartwell, (Crim. No. 328), ante, p. 627, [153 Pac. 730], this day decided. The charge and the evidence were the same in both cases.

Upon the authority of Ex parte Hartwell, the prisoner is discharged.
